B) Install Armadillo (required by ensmallen)

Windows (vcpkg recommended):

git clone https://github.com/microsoft/vcpkg
cd vcpkg
.\bootstrap-vcpkg.bat
.\vcpkg install armadillo


Then build with the vcpkg toolchain:

cd ..\rect_place
cmake -S . -B build -DCMAKE_TOOLCHAIN_FILE=..\vcpkg\scripts\buildsystems\vcpkg.cmake -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release
cmake --build build --config Release


Linux (Debian/Ubuntu):

sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install -y libarmadillo-dev
cd rect_place
cmake -S . -B build -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release
cmake --build build -j

C) Run Panel app

From the project root:

# Make sure the built module is importable:
# On Windows, the .pyd will be under build/Release/; on Linux under build/
# Easiest: run from a shell where PYTHONPATH points to the build output.

# Windows PowerShell example:
$env:PYTHONPATH="$PWD\build\Release;$env:PYTHONPATH"
panel serve python/run_panel.py --show --args input.json

# Linux/macOS:
PYTHONPATH=build:$PYTHONPATH panel serve python/run_panel.py --show --args input.json
